  10 def load_tests(loader, tests, ignore):
  11     # Add the doctests
  12     tests.addTests(DocTestSuite('more_itertools.recipes'))
  13     return tests

 452 class RandomProductTests(TestCase):
 453     """Tests for ``random_product()``
 454 
 455     Since random.choice() has different results with the same seed across
 456     python versions 2.x and 3.x, these tests use highly probably events to
 457     create predictable outcomes across platforms.
 458     """
 459 
 460     def test_simple_lists(self):
 461         """Ensure that one item is chosen from each list in each pair.
 462         Also ensure that each item from each list eventually appears in
 463         the chosen combinations.
 464 
 465         Odds are roughly 1 in 7.1 * 10e16 that one item from either list will
 466         not be chosen after 100 samplings of one item from each list. Just to
 467         be safe, better use a known random seed, too.
 468 
 469         """
 470         nums = [1, 2, 3]
 471         lets = ['a', 'b', 'c']
 472         n, m = zip(*[mi.random_product(nums, lets) for _ in range(100)])
 473         n, m = set(n), set(m)
 474         self.assertEqual(n, set(nums))
 475         self.assertEqual(m, set(lets))
 476         self.assertEqual(len(n), len(nums))
 477         self.assertEqual(len(m), len(lets))
 478 
 479     def test_list_with_repeat(self):
 480         """ensure multiple items are chosen, and that they appear to be chosen
 481         from one list then the next, in proper order.
 482 
 483         """
 484         nums = [1, 2, 3]
 485         lets = ['a', 'b', 'c']
 486         r = list(mi.random_product(nums, lets, repeat=100))
 487         self.assertEqual(2 * 100, len(r))
 488         n, m = set(r[::2]), set(r[1::2])
 489         self.assertEqual(n, set(nums))
 490         self.assertEqual(m, set(lets))
 491         self.assertEqual(len(n), len(nums))
 492         self.assertEqual(len(m), len(lets))
 493

 495 class RandomPermutationTests(TestCase):
 496     """Tests for ``random_permutation()``"""
 497 
 498     def test_full_permutation(self):
 499         """ensure every item from the iterable is returned in a new ordering
 500 
 501         15 elements have a 1 in 1.3 * 10e12 of appearing in sorted order, so
 502         we fix a seed value just to be sure.
 503 
 504         """
 505         i = range(15)
 506         r = mi.random_permutation(i)
 507         self.assertEqual(set(i), set(r))
 508         if i == r:
 509             raise AssertionError("Values were not permuted")
 510 
 511     def test_partial_permutation(self):
 512         """ensure all returned items are from the iterable, that the returned
 513         permutation is of the desired length, and that all items eventually
 514         get returned.
 515 
 516         Sampling 100 permutations of length 5 from a set of 15 leaves a
 517         (2/3)^100 chance that an item will not be chosen. Multiplied by 15
 518         items, there is a 1 in 2.6e16 chance that at least 1 item will not
 519         show up in the resulting output. Using a random seed will fix that.
 520 
 521         """
 522         items = range(15)
 523         item_set = set(items)
 524         all_items = set()
 525         for _ in range(100):
 526             permutation = mi.random_permutation(items, 5)
 527             self.assertEqual(len(permutation), 5)
 528             permutation_set = set(permutation)
 529             self.assertLessEqual(permutation_set, item_set)
 530             all_items |= permutation_set
 531         self.assertEqual(all_items, item_set)
 532

 534 class RandomCombinationTests(TestCase):
 535     """Tests for ``random_combination()``"""
 536 
 537     def test_pseudorandomness(self):
 538         """ensure different subsets of the iterable get returned over many
 539         samplings of random combinations"""
 540         items = range(15)
 541         all_items = set()
 542         for _ in range(50):
 543             combination = mi.random_combination(items, 5)
 544             all_items |= set(combination)
 545         self.assertEqual(all_items, set(items))
 546 
 547     def test_no_replacement(self):
 548         """ensure that elements are sampled without replacement"""
 549         items = range(15)
 550         for _ in range(50):
 551             combination = mi.random_combination(items, len(items))
 552             self.assertEqual(len(combination), len(set(combination)))
 553         self.assertRaises(
 554             ValueError, lambda: mi.random_combination(items, len(items) + 1)
 555         )
 556

 558 class RandomCombinationWithReplacementTests(TestCase):

 561     def test_replacement(self):
 562         """ensure that elements are sampled with replacement"""
 563         items = range(5)
 564         combo = mi.random_combination_with_replacement(items, len(items) * 2)
 565         self.assertEqual(2 * len(items), len(combo))
 566         if len(set(combo)) == len(combo):
 567             raise AssertionError("Combination contained no duplicates")
 568 
 569     def test_pseudorandomness(self):
 570         """ensure different subsets of the iterable get returned over many
 571         samplings of random combinations"""
 572         items = range(15)
 573         all_items = set()
 574         for _ in range(50):
 575             combination = mi.random_combination_with_replacement(items, 5)
 576             all_items |= set(combination)
 577         self.assertEqual(all_items, set(items))

 580 class NthCombinationTests(TestCase):
 581     def test_basic(self):
 582         iterable = 'abcdefg'
 583         r = 4
 584         for index, expected in enumerate(combinations(iterable, r)):
 585             actual = mi.nth_combination(iterable, r, index)
 586             self.assertEqual(actual, expected)
 587 
 588     def test_long(self):
 589         actual = mi.nth_combination(range(180), 4, 2000000)
 590         expected = (2, 12, 35, 126)
 591         self.assertEqual(actual, expected)
 592 
 593     def test_invalid_r(self):
 594         for r in (-1, 3):
 595             with self.assertRaises(ValueError):
 596                 mi.nth_combination([], r, 0)
 597 
 598     def test_invalid_index(self):
 599         with self.assertRaises(IndexError):
 600             mi.nth_combination('abcdefg', 3, -36)

 603 class PrependTests(TestCase):
 604     def test_basic(self):
 605         value = 'a'
 606         iterator = iter('bcdefg')
 607         actual = list(mi.prepend(value, iterator))
 608         expected = list('abcdefg')
 609         self.assertEqual(actual, expected)
 610 
 611     def test_multiple(self):
 612         value = 'ab'
 613         iterator = iter('cdefg')
 614         actual = tuple(mi.prepend(value, iterator))
 615         expected = ('ab',) + tuple('cdefg')
 616         self.assertEqual(actual, expected)
